abstract = {Nuclear particles or light clusters emitted from an excited composite system during the course of its equilibration are termed as pre-equilibrium emission. Few semi-classical and at least one quantum mechanical model have been developed to explain the process of pre-equilibrium emission. Several computer codes based exclusively on the compound reaction mechanism and some including both the compound and the preequilibrium processes are available in the literature. Salient features of some important pre-equilibrium models and details of computer codes frequently used to analyse the experimental data on pre-equilibrium emission are presented in this chapter.},
